1
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:04,168
Why Emmet Ray?
Because he was interesting.

2
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,794
To me, Emmet Ray was
a fascinating character.

3
00:02:06,865 --> 00:02:09,319
I was a huge fan of his
when I was younger.

4
00:02:09,392 --> 00:02:12,240
I thought he was
an absolutely great guitar player...

5
00:02:12,306 --> 00:02:14,161
and he was funny.

6
00:02:14,226 --> 00:02:16,081
You know, or...

7
00:02:16,147 --> 00:02:19,081
if funny's the wrong word,
then sort of pathetic in a way.

8
00:02:19,154 --> 00:02:22,667
He was flamboyant
and he was, you know...

9
00:02:22,738 --> 00:02:24,877
boorish and obnoxious.

10
00:02:24,947 --> 00:02:28,297
Well, the problem is that there's
just so little known about him.

11
00:02:28,372 --> 00:02:31,406
But we do know that
he was a great guitar player.

12
00:02:31,476 --> 00:02:35,666
I'd say he was probably the second
greatest guitar player in the world.

13
00:02:35,732 --> 00:02:37,587
Django Reinhardt was the best...

14
00:02:37,653 --> 00:02:40,239
and believe me,
Emmet idolized Django.

15
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,969
He was in awe of him.

16
00:02:42,038 --> 00:02:46,315
There's a story that says when he
saw him playing in France, he fainted.

17
00:02:46,390 --> 00:02:51,628
He saw Django again at a restaurant
in Germany, and he fainted again.

18
00:02:51,703 --> 00:02:53,296
It seems that every time...

19
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:56,367
Django would always make him faint
or he'd make him cry.

20
00:02:57,080 --> 00:03:00,495
Well, his relationship with Hattie
is mostly what's known about him.

21
00:03:00,568 --> 00:03:03,416
There are a few Emmet Ray
stories before that...

22
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,263
but I have no idea whether
they're true or not.

23
00:03:06,329 --> 00:03:09,014
First time anybody seemed
to have heard of him was in Chicago.

24
00:03:09,082 --> 00:03:11,253
It was at this roadside joint.

25
00:03:15,227 --> 00:03:17,332
Good to see you tonight.

26
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:22,290
- Where the hell is he?
- I don't know.

27
00:03:22,364 --> 00:03:24,819
You gotta get him, Dan.
He's layin' drunk somewhere.

28
00:03:24,892 --> 00:03:27,925
- He's probably in a poolroom.
- Every night it's somethin' else.

29
00:03:27,996 --> 00:03:30,899
He's late. He gets drunk.
He falls off the bandstand.

30
00:03:30,972 --> 00:03:33,940
- I told you not to hire this guy.
- What time does Emmet Ray go on?

31
00:03:34,013 --> 00:03:36,469
Look at the crowd.
Think they're here to see me?

32
00:03:36,542 --> 00:03:38,167
Relax. I'll find him.

33
00:03:38,237 --> 00:03:40,507
I'm gonna have to
hold the show again.

34
00:03:40,574 --> 00:03:43,062
I'll kill this guy.
I don't care what kind of artist he is.

35
00:03:43,134 --> 00:03:46,234
You take care of business.
I'll find him. Just relax.

36
00:03:47,264 --> 00:03:49,370
Hey, good to see you again.

37
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:53,943
That's 50 more you owe me.

38
00:03:54,016 --> 00:03:57,530
I'm not goin' out of town.
Another one?

39
00:04:00,226 --> 00:04:02,330
I think you got some visitors.

40
00:04:04,225 --> 00:04:05,916
I'll be back.

41
00:04:09,634 --> 00:04:11,969
- What'd we get?
- Here's your end.

42
00:04:17,315 --> 00:04:20,699
This is what you bring me, $30?
It's almost midnight. $30?

43
00:04:20,773 --> 00:04:22,628
That's half, Emmet.
That's all we made.

44
00:04:22,693 --> 00:04:25,694
I can't live on that.
I got car payments, I got new shirts.

45
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,700
I'm sorry. Business was slow.
It's a Jewish holiday.

46
00:04:28,773 --> 00:04:32,636
And last night it was rainin', and
the night before you got food poisonin'.

47
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:35,645
- Because I drank that booze you made.
- Listen, Emmet.

48
00:04:35,719 --> 00:04:38,915
I don't know how to tell you this,
but while I was in bed...

49
00:04:38,983 --> 00:04:44,133
with one of the johns you sent me,
he got very excited, and he...

50
00:04:44,199 --> 00:04:47,299
got a heart attack,
and he dropped dead.

51
00:04:48,713 --> 00:04:51,615
- Which one?
- The salesman from Detroit.

52
00:04:51,689 --> 00:04:55,202
- What did you do?
- I took my clothes and I left.

53
00:04:55,273 --> 00:04:57,695
So there's nothin'
to trace back to us?

54
00:04:57,769 --> 00:05:01,796
Then I was thinking that maybe
he had one of your business cards.

55
00:05:02,826 --> 00:05:05,861
- Oh, my God.
- A pimp doesn't need business cards!

56
00:05:05,932 --> 00:05:07,786
You're always tryin'
to be too fancy.

57
00:05:07,851 --> 00:05:10,698
Emmet, let's go.
You're supposed to be on stage.

58
00:05:10,763 --> 00:05:13,862
Every night you're either late,
drunk, or you don't show up.

59
00:05:13,932 --> 00:05:16,071
What is it with you?

60
00:05:27,182 --> 00:05:30,379
How are you doin'?
I'm on right now.

61
00:05:30,447 --> 00:05:32,934
Thanks for comin'.
Put their tab on my bill.

62
00:05:34,191 --> 00:05:37,388
I don't wanna embarrass you in front of
friends, but boss said no more advances.

63
00:05:37,456 --> 00:05:40,522
Don't give me a song and dance.
Just put their tab on my bill.

64
00:05:40,592 --> 00:05:42,251
Hi, guys.

65
00:08:01,829 --> 00:08:05,310
It's gonna be a lot of cats there.
We always have fun at Don's.

66
00:08:05,382 --> 00:08:07,388
- Donald.
- Well, Donald.

67
00:08:07,461 --> 00:08:09,316
- Watch out over there.
- I got this, man.

68
00:08:09,382 --> 00:08:11,717
You take care of that.
And don't forget to pass.

69
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:14,782
- They caught him a couple of times.
- Caught what?

70
00:08:14,854 --> 00:08:17,538
Mind your business.
Watch the road.

71
00:08:17,608 --> 00:08:19,844
What you got there, man?
Is that a.45?

72
00:08:19,911 --> 00:08:22,213
.45 what?
Wait, wait.

73
00:08:23,464 --> 00:08:25,407
Better put that shit away.

74
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:28,864
Hey, you wanna go to the dump,
shoot some rats? Huh?

75
00:08:28,938 --> 00:08:31,109
- Shoot some what?
- Rats.

76
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:33,927
I do it all the time.
It's a lot of fun.

77
00:08:33,994 --> 00:08:37,736
- A hepcat shootin' rats.
- I don't think you need no more of this.

78
00:08:37,801 --> 00:08:42,309
There should be no other guns
in this car besides my gun.

79
00:08:58,861 --> 00:09:01,196
Man, where'd you learn
to play that thing like that?

80
00:09:01,262 --> 00:09:05,005
- I never heard guitar sound so good.
- Yeah, I'm the greatest in the world.

81
00:09:05,071 --> 00:09:07,460
Well, you know,
in France there's Django.

82
00:09:07,535 --> 00:09:11,397
Django? You know, he's comin'
to America in the summer to record.

83
00:09:11,471 --> 00:09:14,570
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Ever meet him?

84
00:09:14,639 --> 00:09:17,061
I could've once, in Europe.

85
00:09:17,136 --> 00:09:19,787
You know, really,
our styles are just different.

86
00:09:19,856 --> 00:09:23,304
Nate Drummond prefers me.
He says I'm miraculous.

87
00:09:23,376 --> 00:09:27,174
You're welcome to come here anytime.
You know, we play here all the time.

88
00:09:27,249 --> 00:09:29,934
- And I make great chili.
- Well, thank you.

89
00:09:47,348 --> 00:09:50,065
Say, man, we're about to hit it.
Can we drop you somewhere?

90
00:09:50,132 --> 00:09:52,402
- I like the air. I'll walk.
- You sure about that?

91
00:09:52,469 --> 00:09:54,324
Yeah. Thank you.

92
00:10:21,817 --> 00:10:24,600
Well, I heard stories
that he was a kleptomaniac.

93
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:28,441
I heard that once he stole
an alarm clock from Hoagy Carmichael...

94
00:10:28,506 --> 00:10:31,190
and Hoagy overslept
and he missed a record date.

95
00:10:31,258 --> 00:10:32,786
What do you think?

96
00:10:32,859 --> 00:10:37,170
The only other story that I heard,
other than Hattie, was this moon idea.

97
00:10:37,244 --> 00:10:40,593
He had this idea
about this crescent moon.

98
00:10:40,668 --> 00:10:43,603
That he wanted to make an entrance
on this big crescent moon.

99
00:10:43,676 --> 00:10:46,906
Well, the story is that
it came to him, apparently...

100
00:10:46,973 --> 00:10:49,079
I guess, in a dream...

101
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:51,540
that he'd build this moon thing
with his own money.

102
00:10:51,614 --> 00:10:54,200
Because he thought that
a star of his great stature...

103
00:10:54,271 --> 00:10:57,948
ought to be able to make
a real big entrance with a moon.

104
00:10:58,015 --> 00:10:59,083
Just try to visualize it.

105
00:10:59,084 --> 00:11:00,151
Just try to visualize it.

106
00:11:00,223 --> 00:11:03,290
You're lookin' up, and there it is.
Gold, beautiful moon.

107
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:06,491
I'm comin' down, and you guys
are playin'. What do you think?

108
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:09,594
It's a stupid idea. I told you.
Would you let me take this shot?

109
00:11:09,664 --> 00:11:13,048
I didn't ask your opinion.
I'm just tellin' you how it's gonna go.

110
00:11:22,786 --> 00:11:25,787
And then the jacket
would match the moon...

111
00:11:25,860 --> 00:11:28,860
against a black
velvet background.

112
00:11:28,932 --> 00:11:32,030
- What do you think?
- It sounds okay to me.

113
00:11:32,099 --> 00:11:34,172
- Yeah.
- It's fancy.

114
00:11:35,588 --> 00:11:38,207
I'm considered
the best guitar player...

115
00:11:38,277 --> 00:11:40,165
maybe that ever lived.

116
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:44,004
Certainly in this country.
There's this...

117
00:11:44,069 --> 00:11:46,458
There's a gypsy in France...

118
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:49,850
and he's the most
beautiful thing I ever heard.

119
00:11:51,815 --> 00:11:53,342
Tonight's the night.

120
00:11:53,415 --> 00:11:56,993
Emmet, just as long as you're happy.
That's the most important thing.

121
00:11:57,063 --> 00:11:58,590
It's really beautiful.

122
00:11:58,663 --> 00:12:01,347
It is really beautiful.
It's like jewelry.

123
00:12:03,049 --> 00:12:06,726
Hey, I wanna just be alone with
the moon for a minute, all right?

124
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:09,640
You wanna be alone
with the moon? Okay.

125
00:12:09,705 --> 00:12:12,520
Emmet, you know what you are?
You're a genius.

126
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,803
She's a knockout, ain't she?

127
00:12:29,869 --> 00:12:31,527
Hope it's safe.

128
00:12:32,493 --> 00:12:35,493
Of course it's safe.
Why wouldn't it be safe?

129
00:12:35,565 --> 00:12:39,656
It's a hell of a drop.
A man can break his neck.

130
00:12:40,494 --> 00:12:42,250
Really?

131
00:12:42,318 --> 00:12:46,181
And it starts to build and build
in Emmet's mind.

132
00:12:46,255 --> 00:12:48,589
And by show time...

133
00:12:48,654 --> 00:12:51,786
he's numb with fear,
he's petrified.

134
00:12:51,855 --> 00:12:54,671
And the audience is out there
waiting for him...

135
00:12:54,736 --> 00:12:57,868
and he's backstage, meanwhile,
drinking and drinking.

136
00:12:57,937 --> 00:13:01,418
When he's ready to go on,
he's stiff as a board.

137
00:13:04,273 --> 00:13:06,608
- Snazzy!
- Did you buy that off the rack?

138
00:13:08,275 --> 00:13:10,130
Look. The Big Dipper.

139
00:13:10,195 --> 00:13:13,991
- Emmet, your gun is bulging.
- Do you think?

140
00:13:14,066 --> 00:13:16,008
What the hell you
need it on stage for?

141
00:13:16,082 --> 00:13:17,992
I don't feel right
without it.

142
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:20,402
I'll give it back to you
as soon as you're done.

143
00:13:20,468 --> 00:13:22,443
Show time!

144
00:13:38,903 --> 00:13:41,325
- You all right?
- Emmet, be careful.

145
00:13:47,896 --> 00:13:49,106
You're on?

146
00:13:50,137 --> 00:13:52,078
Need a hand?

147
00:13:52,152 --> 00:13:53,811
Let's do it.

148
00:14:51,426 --> 00:14:55,617
Sooner or later,
everybody's dreams go up in smoke.

149
00:14:56,321 --> 00:14:58,460
What about my dreams?

150
00:14:58,529 --> 00:15:00,701
I can't settle down, Ann.

151
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:03,226
- We don't have to marry.
- I can't.

152
00:15:03,299 --> 00:15:06,300
I gotta be free.
I'm an artist.

153
00:15:06,372 --> 00:15:08,543
I thought you liked me.

154
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:11,715
We have fun.

155
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:15,610
I took you to the dump.
I let you shoot my gun at some rats.

156
00:15:15,685 --> 00:15:18,948
Shootin' rats at the dump
is not my idea of a good time.

157
00:15:19,014 --> 00:15:21,251
Why not?
We brought sandwiches.

158
00:15:21,318 --> 00:15:24,864
And sittin' at the railroads watchin'
trains, that's pretty strange too.

159
00:15:24,935 --> 00:15:28,514
See? That's what I mean.

160
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:32,380
What I like to do, what you like to do,
ain't the same thing.

161
00:15:32,455 --> 00:15:34,179
That's not it, Emmet.

162
00:15:34,247 --> 00:15:36,254
It's that you keep
your feelings locked up...

163
00:15:36,327 --> 00:15:39,045
and you can't feel nothin'
for anybody else.

164
00:15:39,112 --> 00:15:41,185
You say that
like it's a bad thing.

165
00:15:41,257 --> 00:15:45,765
Some terrible things happen
to people in love. I know. I've seen it.

166
00:15:45,834 --> 00:15:48,997
I enjoy the company of women.
I love 'em.

167
00:15:49,065 --> 00:15:52,295
It's just that
I don't need 'em.

168
00:15:52,362 --> 00:15:56,138
I guess, you know, that's the way it is
when you're a true artist.

169
00:15:58,764 --> 00:16:01,065
It doesn't mean
we can't fool around.

170
00:16:01,131 --> 00:16:04,678
Oh, right.
Or shoot rats or watch trains.

171
00:16:04,749 --> 00:16:08,775
I never met anybody that
keeps their feelings so locked up.

172
00:16:08,845 --> 00:16:11,529
I let my feelin's
come out in my music.

173
00:16:11,597 --> 00:16:15,820
Maybe if you let your feelings out in
real life, your music would be better.

174
00:16:15,885 --> 00:16:17,478
Don't talk.

175
00:16:21,231 --> 00:16:23,752
Emmet met Hattie in New Jersey.

176
00:16:23,823 --> 00:16:26,725
The band was playing a resort hotel.

177
00:16:26,799 --> 00:16:29,418
On a day off, Emmet...

178
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:33,067
and his drummer,
Bill Shields...

179
00:16:33,137 --> 00:16:35,526
were doing their
version of charm.

180
00:16:35,601 --> 00:16:38,536
They were trying to pick up girls
on the boardwalk.

181
00:16:41,809 --> 00:16:44,427
This place is heaven on earth.
Cotton candy, eight o'clock.

182
00:16:44,497 --> 00:16:46,025
Watch me work.

183
00:16:46,930 --> 00:16:49,320
Mary! Right?

184
00:16:49,395 --> 00:16:51,729
Why don't you drop dead, jerk?

185
00:16:51,795 --> 00:16:55,505
I thought you were someone I knew.
Sometimes I hit with a... Mary!

186
00:16:55,571 --> 00:16:57,230
Martina. Mary Ann.

187
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:59,123
Marge. Kate?

188
00:16:59,188 --> 00:17:02,287
Excuse me, miss.
I'm a photography buff myself.

189
00:17:02,357 --> 00:17:05,324
I was thinkin' maybe we could
get my friend to take a picture of us.

190
00:17:05,397 --> 00:17:07,253
Wait a minute. Time out.

191
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:09,490
- Do you see this?
- Oh, yeah.

192
00:17:09,558 --> 00:17:12,308
Did you see? She looked
right at me. She smiled.

193
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:15,342
- That was a smile.
- And she was lookin' right at me.

194
00:17:15,414 --> 00:17:16,821
Which one you want?

195
00:17:16,887 --> 00:17:18,642
The little one
with the silly hat.

196
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,565
She's more my size.
I'll flip you.

197
00:17:20,631 --> 00:17:22,736
- I saw her first!
- All right!

198
00:17:22,807 --> 00:17:25,175
You want the little one?
Take the little one.

199
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,183
I'll take the redhead.
What difference does it make?

200
00:17:27,256 --> 00:17:30,552
They're gettin' away. There's
nothin' wrong with the little one.

201
00:17:30,617 --> 00:17:33,367
The redhead's got
nice legs and a nice chest.

202
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:35,474
- I'll take the redhead.
- The little one is cute.

203
00:17:35,546 --> 00:17:39,343
She has a nice face and those Cupid-bow
lips I like, but I'll take the redhead.

204
00:17:39,418 --> 00:17:41,012
- You wanted the little one.
- I changed my mind.

205
00:17:41,083 --> 00:17:42,609
I'll flip you.

206
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:46,324
- Call.
- Tails.

207
00:17:49,564 --> 00:17:51,703
- I got the little one.
- We agree.

208
00:17:51,772 --> 00:17:54,074
- Now they gotta agree.
- Come on.

209
00:17:55,516 --> 00:17:58,451
I'm telling you, you're gonna
get on the Ferris wheel this time.

210
00:17:58,524 --> 00:18:02,170
Remember when you tried to go on?
Last year we tried to get you up there.

211
00:18:02,238 --> 00:18:04,093
- Excuse me.
- You were scared.

212
00:18:04,158 --> 00:18:07,323
Hi. You ladies from around here?

213
00:18:07,391 --> 00:18:09,463
Yeah, we work right near here.

214
00:18:09,534 --> 00:18:12,120
I'm Billy Shields.
I'm a musician.

215
00:18:12,191 --> 00:18:15,061
He's with my quintet.
I'm Emmet Ray.

216
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:17,471
The Emmet Ray Hot Quintet.
We're at the Lakeside Ballroom.

217
00:18:17,536 --> 00:18:21,398
It's our day off, so we were thinking
maybe you could show us the sights.

218
00:18:21,472 --> 00:18:24,287
- You wanna go watch some trains?
- What?

219
00:18:24,352 --> 00:18:27,255
He's kidding.
Let's go for a drink.

220
00:18:28,705 --> 00:18:31,357
Ask him. I liked you instantly.
I'm bein' honest.

221
00:18:31,426 --> 00:18:33,499
We flipped, he won, I got you.

222
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:35,807
I'm Gracie MacRae.

223
00:18:35,874 --> 00:18:37,248
Billy Shields.

224
00:18:37,315 --> 00:18:41,244
And if I may say, you have the most
beautiful blue eyes I've ever seen.

225
00:18:41,315 --> 00:18:43,585
This is my friend Hattie.

226
00:18:43,652 --> 00:18:45,757
Hattie, I'm Emmet Ray.

227
00:18:45,828 --> 00:18:49,057
I've got the quintet.
You like jazz music, baby?

228
00:18:49,124 --> 00:18:51,808
How about we take
a boat ride, huh?

229
00:18:51,877 --> 00:18:54,430
Well, sure.
We'd love to.

230
00:18:54,502 --> 00:18:56,924
- We'll ride around the lake.
- Great.

231
00:18:56,998 --> 00:18:59,812
What's your name?
Don't be shy, darlin'.

